    <mainBody>
      <paragraph eId="para_6" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>1.</num>
        <content eId="para_6__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Takes note</span> of the report of the Secretary-General;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_7" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>2.</num>
        <content eId="para_7__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Welcomes</span> the progress made by the United Nations System Staff College, over the past two years, in providing high-quality learning and training opportunities to United Nations staff and to relevant partners of the United Nations system;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_9" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>3.</num>
        <content eId="para_9__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recognizes</span> the important role played by the Staff College through inter‑agency capacity-building, in support of the United Nations priorities and learning needs, in particular in the areas of economic and social development, peace and security and internal management;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_12" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>4.</num>
        <content eId="para_12__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Commends</span> the Staff College for its ability to develop a hub of learning management platforms and e-learning offerings that increase the coherence and cost-efficiency of the United Nations system through the pooling of learning resources and the identification of common capacity gaps;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_16" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>5.</num>
        <content eId="para_16__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Notes with appreciation</span> the development of training on the capabilities required to promote agility, integration and cohesion across the system and to offer system-wide solutions to the current challenges, including in the areas of innovation, data, digital transformation, strategic foresight and behavioural science;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_21" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>6.</num>
        <content eId="para_21__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Acknowledges</span> the continued efforts of the Staff College to ensure its sustainability, including through self-generated resources, and encourages the international community to strengthen its support to the College through voluntary contributions, in accordance with article VII of its statute;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_27" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>7.</num>
        <content eId="para_27__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Reaffirms</span> the role of the Staff College as a catalyst for leadership development, organizational change, innovation and transformation within the United Nations system;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_34" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>8.</num>
        <content eId="para_34__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Calls upon</span> all organizations of the United Nations system to make full use of the services provided by the Staff College, to coordinate their learning and training activities with the Staff College and to encourage the participation of their staff in relevant Staff College courses, thus enhancing the overall efficiency and cost-effectiveness of learning in the United Nations system;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_42" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>9.</num>
        <content eId="para_42__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Encourages</span> the Staff College, in line with its inter-agency mandate, to collaborate with relevant United Nations entities to identify opportunities for greater coherence and efficiency in the learning function across the United Nations system, such as through the provision of common learning services aimed at enhancing system-wide effectiveness and complementarity;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_51" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>10.</num>
        <content eId="para_51__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Also encourages</span> the Staff College to enhance its cooperation with relevant entities outside the United Nations system, in accordance with article II, paragraph 2, of its statute, and in particular with academic institutions worldwide, to further enrich its learning offerings;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_61" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>11.</num>
        <content eId="para_61__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Encourages</span> Member States to continue to support the Staff College by recognizing its unique inter-agency function and its demonstrated ability to build the capacity of United Nations staff and relevant partners for the effective and efficient delivery of their mandates. </p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
